commit.message:
clear SSL error on unexpected eof during read

(fix noxxi/p5-io-socket-ssl#145)

handle SSL shutdown errors in blocking mode too

(fix noxxi/p5-io-socket-ssl#144)

localize $! in ossl_trace to avoid heisenbug

(fix noxxi/p5-io-socket-ssl#143)

fix stop_SSL not checking SSL_WANT_WRITE

(fix noxxi/p5-io-socket-ssl#142)

Adapt to new OpenSSL version / ABI compatibility scheme

https://www.openssl.org/policies/releasestrat.html

In short, as of 3.0.0, when the version is MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH,
only changes in MAJOR indicate API/ABI incompatible changes.

Fixes: https://github.com/noxxi/p5-io-socket-ssl/issues/137
Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/show_bug.cgi?id=909545
Signed-off-by: Andreas K. Hüttel <dilfridge@gentoo.org>

commit.message: Fix typos

return undef from get_fingerprint_bin if no certificate given and no peer
certificate known #136

- release as 2.083
- fix t/protocol_version.t for OpenSSL versions which don't support SECLEVEL
  (regression from #122)
release as 2.082
update fingerprints for external tests

set TLS version default to TLS 1.2+ since TLS 1.1 and lower are officially deprecated #122
adjust t/protocol_version.t to explicitly set SECLEVEL=2 in order to test with older versions
further improved regex for hostname
